sentences: Eric Vloeimans (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈeːrɪk ˈvluimɑns]; born 24 March 1963) is a Dutch musician, songwriter, and record producer.
After graduating in 1988, he moved to New York City and studied trumpet with Donald Byrd.
In the 1990s, he recorded the album Bitches and Fairy Tales (1999) with Marc Johnson, Joey Baron, and John Taylor.
